5000|$|Perfect North {{was formed}} by the Perfect Family and others in 1980. Initially funded by the sale of cattle by Clyde & Ella Mae Perfect, it began with 2 handle tows and a rope tow on two <b>ski</b> <b>runs</b> on the [...] "big" [...] hill, as well as 2 rope tows on the bunny slope. In 1984, a chair was added where the [...] "big" [...] rope tow was, and another chair was added in 1985. In 1987, Perfect North added their third chairlift, which added one blue square and two black diamond <b>ski</b> <b>runs.</b> Eventually, they added two more chairs, {{including}} their 5th chair, which opened up 4 new <b>ski</b> <b>runs.</b>|$|R
